{"article_id":"VE7CHr5E594xSxEu","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The Senate on Friday voted to block any witnesses from being called in President Donald Trump 's impeachment trial , a move","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that marked the beginning of the end of the third Senate trial for a president in US history .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"Senate leaders struck an agreement","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"to hold the final vote","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"to acquit Trump on the two articles of impeachment","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"at 4 p.m . ET on Wednesday ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"following a debate throughout the day on Friday","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"about how to bring the trial to a close .","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"The impeachment trial will resume on Monday .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"The timing means","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"that the acquittal vote will occur","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"after Trump comes up to Capitol Hill","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"to deliver the State of the Union address on Tuesday evening .","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"The Senate approved a resolution Friday evening from Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"laying out the final steps for the trial .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"The resolution includes closing arguments of two hours each for the House managers and the President 's legal team","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"starting at 11 a.m. on Monday , Wednesday 's final vote","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"-- and the ability","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"for senators to deliver their own speeches","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"explaining their votes in between .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Republicans defeated four Democratic amendments to McConnell 's resolution on Friday evening","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"before breaking for the weekend","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"-- a schedule","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"that would allow senators","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"who are Democratic presidential candidates","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"to travel to Iowa this weekend ahead of Monday 's Iowa caucuses .","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"Republican senators said","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"the Kentucky Republican had no choice","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"but to cut the deal for the Wednesday acquittal vote","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"because Democrats could have used their power under the rules","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"to drag out the process past Tuesday 's State of the Union .","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"And Democrats had no desire","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"to let Trump be cleared by the time of his address","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"as the White House wanted ,","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"according to senators from both parties .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"So they decided to cut the deal ,","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"spare themselves late nights and a weekend session ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"and agree to have the vote on Wednesday .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"`` Democrats were willing to use any number of dilatory tactics ,","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"many of which would probably carry us into next week , ''","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"said Sen. John Thune of South Dakota , the No . 2 Senate Republican .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"The Senate vote Friday","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"to allow subpoenas for witnesses and documents","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"failed 49-51 ,","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"with two Republicans , Sens . Susan Collins of Maine and Mitt Romney of Utah , joining Democrats","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"to back extending the trial .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"The Senate went into an extended break","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"after the debate on the witness vote concluded","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"but before the vote ,","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"while McConnell and Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer huddled on the floor","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"while their staffs hammer out the details on the trial endgame .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"Democrats had hoped to entice more other Senate Republicans to join them","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"to hear from witnesses","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"-- especially in the wake of revelations from the draft book manuscript of former national security adviser John Bolton --","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"but one by one the Senate Republicans said","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"they were ready to end the trial .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"Their reasons differed .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"Sen. Lisa Murkowski , an Alaska Republican , said in a statement :","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"`` I do n't believe","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"the continuation of this process will change anything .","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"It is sad for me to admit","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"that , as an institution , the Congress has failed . ''","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"Sen. Lamar Alexander of Tennessee , meanwhile , said","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"the House managers had proven their case","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"that Trump withheld US aid","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"while pushing for an investigation into his political rivals .","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"`` The question is whether you apply capital punishment to every offense .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"And I think","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"in this case ,","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"I think","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"the answer is no ,","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"let the people make that decision , ''","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"Alexander said Friday .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"When the final vote does occur","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"to acquit the President ,","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"it will mark the end of a remarkable , whirlwind four-month impeachment","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"that began","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"when House Speaker Nancy Pelosi announced an impeachment inquiry on September 24 ,","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"leading to the President 's impeachment on two articles","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"-- abuse of power and obstruction of Congress --","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"less than three months later .","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"After a month delay , the Senate trial began less than two weeks ago .","depth":5},{"id":83,"text":"The House managers ,","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"led by House Intelligence Chairman Adam Schiff ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"presented a detailed case","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"arguing","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"they had overwhelming evidence","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"that Trump withheld $ 400 million in US security aid and a White House meeting with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"while he pressured Kiev to open investigations into former Vice President Joe Biden and his son Hunter Biden .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"`` If the Senate allows President Trump 's obstruction to stand ,","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"it effectively nullifies the impeachment power , ''","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"Schiff said Friday .","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"`` It will allow future presidents to decide","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"whether they want their misconduct to be investigated or not ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"whether they would like to participate in an impeachment investigation or not . ''","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"The President 's team argued","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"there was no wrongdoing","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"-- but also that","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"even if there was a quid pro quo ,","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"it was within the President 's rights","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"if it was in the national interest .","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"`` The problem with the case , the problem with their position , is","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"even with all of those witnesses , it does n't prove up an impeachable offense .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"The articles fail , ''","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"the President 's personal attorney Jay Sekulow said .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"`` They got the wish of the impeachment by Christmas ,","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"and that is goal .","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"But now they want you to do the work","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"they failed to do . ''","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"Collins and the other Republican moderates included a provision in the Senate trial rules","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"to allow for Friday 's witness vote ,","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"but the odds looked long for Democrats to convert four Republicans to back the vote until Sunday -","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"when The New York Times reported","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"Bolton 's draft book manuscript","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"alleged","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"that Trump told him","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"the US security aid was conditioned on investigations into Democrats ,","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"including Joe Biden .","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"On Friday , new allegations came from The Times from Bolton 's manuscript","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"-","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"that Trump directed Bolton to help his attorney Rudy Giuliani get in touch with the Ukrainian president in May -","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"which Schiff cited during Friday 's witness debate .","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"McConnell , however , held his conference together enough","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"to keep the witness vote at bay ,","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"with Alexander the linchpin of his bend-but-not break strategy .","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"Until Thursday , Alexander did not tip his hand on which way he was leaning ,","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"declining to speak to reporters about it","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"and staying quiet in GOP conference meetings .","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"He finally asked two questions at the tail end of the two-day Senate question period in the trial ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"which hinted at his eventual position","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"to oppose witnesses .","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"Shortly before Alexander 's statement , Collins became the first Republican","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"to back witnesses .","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"`` I believe","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"hearing from certain witnesses would give each side the opportunity","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"to more fully and fairly make their case ,","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"resolve any ambiguities ,","depth":13},{"id":138,"text":"and provide additional clarity , ''","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"Collins said .","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"Romney joined her","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"in crossing the aisle for Friday 's vote ,","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"but that left Democrats two short of what they needed","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"to call witnesses .","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"Murkowski 's statement implicitly acknowledged","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"had she voted for witnesses ,","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"the vote could have ended 50-50 ,","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"dragging Chief Justice John Roberts into the fray .","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"`` It has also become clear some of my colleagues intend to further politicize this process ,","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"and drag the Supreme Court into the fray ,","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"while attacking the Chief Justice , ''","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"Murkowski said .","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"`` I will not stand for nor support that effort .","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"We have already degraded this institution for partisan political benefit ,","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"and I will not enable those","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"who wish to pull down another . ''","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"On the Democratic side , there are still a couple of undecided senators on the vote for conviction ,","depth":6},{"id":158,"text":"including Sens . Doug Jones of Alabama and Joe Manchin of West Virginia .","depth":6},{"id":159,"text":"Jones said Friday","depth":8},{"id":160,"text":"he was `` pretty close '' to a decision ,","depth":8},{"id":161,"text":"while Manchin said","depth":8},{"id":162,"text":"he has n't yet made one .","depth":8},{"id":163,"text":"`` It 's a very hard decision , ''","depth":8},{"id":164,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":165,"text":"`` It 's most serious decision","depth":8},{"id":166,"text":"that any senator will make in their career . ''","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":333,"left":0,"right":332,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":332,"left":239,"right":331,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":239,"left":207,"right":238,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":207,"left":186,"right":206,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":179,"right":185,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":168,"right":178,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":173,"right":177,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":3,"right":172,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":170,"right":171,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":169,"right":6,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":169,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":9,"right":176,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":10,"right":175,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":175,"left":11,"right":174,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left"